.TH HOW 1 "February 2026" "how" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
how \- ask technical questions from the shell using an LLM

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B how
[\fIquestion\fR...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B how
sends a question to a configured language model and renders
the response as a manual page.

If standard input is not attached to a TTY, its contents are
appended to the question.

The output is piped into a viewer command (default:
.BR "man -l -" ).

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDE_API_KEY
API key used for Claude authentication.

.TP
.B HOW_VIEWER_CMD
Command used to display output. The generated text is piped
to this command.

.TP
.B HOW_SYSTEM_PROMPT
Overrides the default system prompt used when generating
responses.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.

.TP
.B 1
realloc() failure.

.TP
.B 2
socket() failure.

.TP
.B 3
Specified host not found.

.TP
.B 4
SSL connect failure

.TP
.B 5
malloc() failure.

.TP
.B 6
SSL_send() failure.

.TP
.B 7
SSL_recv() failure.

.TP
.B 8
Key database retrieve failure.

.TP
.B 9
General API failures.

.TP
.B 10
Failure during stdio reading.

.SH EXAMPLES
Ask a question:

.nf
how how to fork in C
.fi

Multiline input:

.nf
how <<EOF
Explain this program:
int main() { return 0; }
EOF
.fi

Pipe input:

.nf
cat file.c | how explain this code
.fi

